Hi John,

I don't understand one thing, actually there is a lot I don't understand,
but I'll start with one question at a time. 

If I have a 200mm 6V flywheel, why would I need to grind out the bellhousing
to fit a 12V flywheel in there? Aren't they both 200mm?
	
My long-term plan is to go 12V. I now need a new starter, so I figure
instead of getting another 6V, I could just get a 12V with a bushing
adaptor. Although I do like the idea of a 6V starter on a 12V engine-I have
heard you get great powerful starts, even when it's really cold out.

-Kevin

